學院依據學生的報讀人數，時間表安排及可用資源而決定每學期所開辦的學科。









Evanna Ling

2016-2017 Associate of Arts in Media, Cultural and Creative Studies - Media and Cultural Studies
Offer accepted: HKU Bachelor of Arts in Global Creative Industries, year 3
Other Offers received: CUHK Bachelor of Arts in Cultural Studies, year 3
Other Offers received: CityU Bachelor of Social Sciences- Public Policy and Politics, year 3
Other Offers received: CityU Bachelor of  Social Sciences-  Asian and International Studies, year 3
Other Offers received: City U Bachelor of Arts Linguistics and Language Applications, year 3
Other Offers received: HKBU Bachelor of Arts (Hons) in Creative & Professional Writing
Other Offers received: PolyU Bachelor of Arts in Social Policy and Politics, year 3


Cultural Studies courses provided by the HKUSPACE laid a solid foundation for my advanced academic pursuit. Courses in popular culture, city branding, the relationship between gender and society, heritage and tourism strengthened my academic foundation of cultural theories and inspired me to view everyday life, politics, and discourse from multiple perspectives. This interdisciplinary way of thinking is what I wish to develop in Global Creative Industries.






Christy Chang

2015-2017 Associate of Arts in Media, Cultural and Creative Studies – Media and Cultural Studies
Offer accepted: CUHK Bachelor of Arts in Cultural Studies, year 3
Other offers received: HKU Bachelor of Arts in Comparative Literature, year 3
Other offers received: CityU Bachelor of Social Sciences in Asian and International Studies, year 3


During the two-year study at SPACE, what I gained most was advice from lecturers. Especially cultural domain lecturers, they are willing to discuss with your points of your assignments or even listen to you with your problems. A school life is never only acquiring knowledge, but also building up relationships.






Heather Au

2015-2017 Associate of Arts in Media, Cultural and Creative Studies – Media and Cultural Studies
Offer accepted: HKU Bachelor of Arts in Comparative Literature, year3
Other offers received: HKBU Bachelor of Arts in Humanities, year 3


MCS exposes me to a new and critical approach to popular culture and daily practices. The concepts are not difficult to understand if you could pay attention to the lectures and try to apply them in any cultural phenomenon.  Keep thinking and questioning the things around you outside the lecture!






Cassie Chan

2015-2017 Associate of Arts in Media, Cultural and Creative Studies – Media and Cultural Studies
