As a business and science student in secondary education, I had never thought of studying in arts fields. I think it is essential to discover and choose a programme based on our own interests in tertiary education so we will gain plenty of enjoyment but not anxieties in future.






Chu Ho Ting

2015-2016 Associate of Arts in Media, Cultural and Creative Studies
Offer accepted: HKU - BA programme in Global Creative Industries Year 3
Offer received: CUHK - Bachelor of Social Science in Gender Studies Year 1 (2-year program)


HKU SPACE CC has been a great place for me to obtain knowledge about our everyday life. Our daily practices have their own origin, and everything that seems normal is actually ideological. What I learned here is the way to uncover hidden meanings behind these practices. I am pretty sure you will see the world in a completely different perspective, and what you usually see every day will never be the same after studying here.






Alicia Gao

2014 文學副學士（媒體、文化及創意）　一年級
2015 - 嶺南大學 文學院 二年級 （副學士一年級升上大學二年級）


“Learning is the eye of the mind”. If you love to acquire new knowledge and skills and believe that lifelong learning is a key to meeting your goals - HKU SPACE CC would be your top choice. There are knowledgeable professors, mentors, and counsellors who always help you to achieve your dreams.






Kam Wing Sze, Cathy

2012-2014 文學副學士（媒體、文化及創意）
